Twist, Glide, Protect: Unleash the Power of the Liquid Screen Protector Pen! Introducing the new, patent-pending TWIST PEN Liquid Screen Protector, an innovative breakthrough in the realm of device safety. This innovative TWIST PEN design simplifies the application process to just twist, glide, and protect. The efficient design ensures a flawlessly smooth, bubble-free application, culminating in an almost imperceptible, microscopic shield that embraces every inch of your screen. The protective solution, supercharged with silicon dioxide nanoparticles and our exclusive additional component, seamlessly bonds to your screen, forming a fortress against scratches, cracks, and the strains of everyday use. Adding to the TWIST PEN Liquid Glass Screen Protector's advantages is its impressive coverage capacity. With the ability to protect up to 10 devices, it stands as a cost-effective solution for tech aficionados or multi-device households. To further enhance the protection process, each TWIST PEN comes bundled with a high-quality screen cleaner spray. This aids in preparing your device for the optimal adherence of the advanced protective solution, ensuring a pristine and flawless application. Unlike traditional tempered glass protectors, our TWIST PEN design eliminates the struggle with alignment, bubbles, and dust particles. It simplifies the application process to just twist, glide, and protect, ensuring a flawlessly smooth, bubble-free application. This efficient design forms a microscopic, almost imperceptible shield that extends across every inch of your screen, offering comprehensive coverage and superior protection. Step into the new era of screen protection with the TWIST PEN Liquid Glass Screen Protector. More than just a product, it's a revolutionary shift in device safety, offering unparalleled protection and extraordinary ease of use. Welcome to a new dawn in screen protection, where advanced technology and convenience converge to create the ultimate protective shield for your device. .

Nanotech Mastery: How TWIST PEN Reinforces Your Screen on a Microscopic Scale TWIST PEN Liquid Screen Protector: Harnessing Microscopic Science for Unparalleled Screen Defense Even under a microscope, the surface of a device's glass screen reveals an array of subtle ridges and valleys. These microscopic inconsistencies are inherent to glass production, and they can become points of vulnerability when your device encounters the strains of daily use. This is where the magic of the TWIST PEN Liquid Screen Protector comes into play. The TWIST PEN's protective solution, imbued with a potent fusion of advanced SiO2 technology and a unique proprietary component, is designed to work in harmony with these natural contours of your screen. Upon application, this remarkable compound enhances the existing glass surface, boosting its inherent durability by weaving itself into the screen's existing architecture.The result is a screen surface that's not just protected, but fortified. The TWIST PEN Liquid Screen Protector effectively mitigates the inherent weak points in the glass, strengthening its resistance to everyday wear and tear. With this added resilience, your screen becomes tougher and more robust, its enhanced hardness offering superior protection against scratches and damage from everyday use. .

Effortless APPLICATION – Twist, Glide, Protect CLEAN Thoroughly clean all glass surfaces using the provided cleaning spray and microfiber cloth, ensuring that the screen is free of any dust, smudges, or debris. APPLY Open the Twist Pen's cap. Holding the Twist Pen on top of the screen, twist the back end multiple times until liquid is dispensed onto the brush tip. Then, apply the solution gently onto the screen using smooth strokes, ensuring coverage across the entire screen. It does NOT have to be spread perfectly even. DRY Allow the glass surface to cure for at least 30 minutes (While 30 minutes is enough, leaving the coating on overnight to allow it to bond and cure may yield better results. BUFF Use the supplied microfiber cloth to buff the glass surface in a circular motion to remove any residues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I'm not impressed
reviews.reviewText: I bought this product to use on an older iPad that my child uses, wanting to have a little extra protection for the screen in addition to a screen protector. I followed the instructions, though they are vague where it comes to the application. Do I twist the cap clockwise or counter-clockwise? Clockwise just clicked. Counter-clockwise seemed to hit resistance. I'm assuming the idea is like operating a tube of chapstick or glue, that when you rotate the cap it puts pressure on the liquid to come out of the brush. Well that never really happened for me. It did a few large drops of liquid, but really the brush was almost dry the whole time. I attempted the application anyway, but like the other reviewed mentioned, it just left a lot of streaks on the iPad, and after an hour I cleaned the streaks away and want to move on without this product. The internal mechanism that the twist top engages with broke, so that might be part of the problem, so if that's the case, I think the manufacturer has some quality control work to do with this product. I did not reach out to the manufacturer to ask for a replacement because even with the little bit of application I attempted, I am not convinced this product performs as advertised. I did reach out to Amazon for a refund because the product broke, so I have initiated the return process. Feedback for manufacturer: better instructions, application videos so we know what the application process should look like... are we dry-brushing this product on, or is it supposed to be coated in liquid?
